<div class="border border-line rounded-2xl p-6 md:p-[34px] bg-paper" style="animation:tl-reveal linear both;animation-timeline:view();animation-range:entry 0% cover 30%;">
  <div class="font-mono text-xs tracking-[.12em] uppercase text-accent mb-4">the name</div>
  <div class="font-serif text-[30px] font-semibold mb-1">tump·line</div>
  <div class="font-mono text-[13px] text-muted mb-[18px]">/ˈtʌmplaɪn/ &nbsp;·&nbsp; noun</div>
  <p class="text-[17px] leading-[1.62] text-ink m-0 mb-[14px] italic">A strap worn across the forehead or chest to carry a heavy load.</p>
  <p class="text-base leading-[1.62] text-muted m-0">For centuries, Indigenous peoples and voyageurs across Canada used the tumpline to move more with less strain — distributing weight so the body could go further. A fitting name for taking the technical weight off your team so it can keep moving.</p>
